replies.bodyText:
Hmm, maybe we could create a single notification manager object in DownloadService that does something like this in onCreate?
syncExecutor.execute(() -> newEpisodeNotification.loadCounters());

syncExecutor is a single background thread, so if posting the method call to that thread is the first thing that the DownloadService does, we can be sure that the counters are loaded before the first feed is parsed.
Then it could do something like this in handleSuccessfulDownload:
newEpisodeNotification.displayIfNecessary(request);

The problem is that we can not really do database things in onDestroy. The method itself is called on the main thread and it needs to shut down the executors. So the easiest method would be to do this in handleSuccessfulDownload, I think.

